HEADWORD: low-lying
<hw>low-lying</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having a small
elevation above the ground or horizon or sea level; <as>as,
<ex>low-lying</ex> clouds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>at a low elevation above sea level.</def>⟦br⟧
